    Supplies BugChecker instances. Allows us to abstract over different ways of acquiring BugCheckers, for example, by reflectively instantiating them from their Classes vs. already having an instance. Additionally provides information about the checker, including canonical name, severity, maturity, and whether the checker may be disabled.
